Package: Rpkg.exam
Type: Package
Title: R package to get by through the course
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Petr Houska
Maintainer: The package maintainer <p.houska@gmail.com>
Description: 
    This package serves the sole purpose of getting me through the course Intermediate R
    On linux you might have to install libmagick++-dev
    Usage of this is package:
    grayscale_image <- Rgrayscale("path to an image")
      gives an grayscale image of submitted image
    split_image <- Rsplit("path to an image")  
      gives a named list of images, that can be accessed ie. through split_image$RGB
    test image is provided in samples/Test image-1.jpg
    try i.e. print(grayscale_image) or print(split_image$R)
